$interpreted: Jia-Shen: The houses have already been torn down!? Didn't he say three days!
Pang: No doubt that young hooligan never intended on keeping his word!
Child: ——Mr. Tiger!!!
Child: Mr. Tiger! Where'd you go!?
Pang: What happened, dear child?
Child: That fellow named Humpty, he brought soldiers here to tear down the houses.
Child: Granny Xica and several others were terribly upset and said they were going to Humpty's house for justice to be served, and then...*sob*...*sob*...
Jia-Shen: And then what happened!? Speak!
Local: Then, they never came back...we couldn't find them anywhere in the city...
Jia-Shen: ——No way Humpty locked them up!?
Pang: What are we waiting for? Let's go save them!
Pang: What's wrong?
Jia-Shen: You know what you're saying, right? You want us to bust into a noble's home...
Jia-Shen: Even if Meemaw and them are in Humpty's house, we're still gonna get all sorts o' punished.
Pang: It's no time for such words.
Jia-Shen: But...them fancy folks are nobles, we can commit no offense 'gainst them...
Jia-Shen: Or maybe we got it all wrong, they might just come back in a 'lil bit...
Pang: SHAMELESS!!!
Pang: Their lives' are priceless, and yet you blabber on, unwilling to fulfill your duties!
Jia-Shen: Not everyone is as great as you...
Pang: What's that got to do with it!
Pang: This has nothing to do with abilities, you've got no heart, that's all. And if something happens to Granny Xica, how will you face her?
Jia-Shen: But...it's just...
Pang: Enough!
Pang: If you want to be like every other turtle, who shrink into themselves at the slightest sign of danger, then so be it!
Jia-Shen: I-I-I...I'm not a turtle...
Jia-Shen: I'm not a turtle, I'm a tortoise!

Granny Xica: Let us go! We did nothing illegal. In fact, it was you who has broken the law! 

We were merely protesting, and yet you've punished us without the requisite authority!
Local: That's right!
Local: Coming in and tearing down our houses while we're resting! Despicable!
Humpty: Shut up. So I punished you of my own accord, so what? What are you gonna do about it? No one dares come into MY house!
Pang: ...I'll take responsibility for everything.
Jia-Shen: You mean...!?
Pang: So as long as he can't charge you with breaking into a noble's place of residence, you'll do it?
Jia-Shen: Yessir. So long as there's no proof that I've participated...but what about you? Humpty won't let this go...
Pang: I'm already a wanted man. One more crime won't make a difference.
Pang: I'll get the attention of the security guards outside. I'll leave the rest up to you.
Jia-Shen: ...Wait a sec!
Jia-Shen: Head east.
Jia-Shen: On the eastern side of the Kingdom of the Sun, there's an unregulated Desert Bazaar. There, they won't be able to do anything to you.
Jia-Shen: ...Thanks.
Pang: We must be kind to one another, for we are all fighting a hard battle. We'll meet again someday.
Pang: RARGHH!!!!
Humpty: You stinkin' cat! Once again messing in my affairs! GET HIM!!
Jia-Shen: Is everyone alright? Let me help ya'll get these ropes off.
Granny Xica: ...Is that...Jia-Shen...?
Jia-Shen: Humpty!? You...how could you——
Humpty: Hehe, truly worthy of the name turtle trash. Even your battle tactics stink like trash. You thought you could get my attention and draw me out of here?
Humpty: What's the matter? Still haven't shrunk into your shell and run off like a baby?
Humpty: You must know, a poor eastern student like you, publicly resisting a Desert noble; that only can mean trouble for you.
Granny Xica: Jia-Shen...
Jia-Shen: Humpty...let them go.
Humpty: You filthy coward; you dare give me orders?
Humpty: You're guilty of breaking into a noble's residence——get him!
Humpty: Bottom feeding turtle trash, you dare hit me!!!
Jia-Shen: I may be trash, but even trash has dignity. And I've got people to protect!
？？？: Well said.
